          <avActivityHighlights>As a consequence of warming moist small and medium sized avalanches are to be expected. &lt;br/&gt; The wind slabs can be released, especially at their margins, in particular on steep shady slopes. Weak layers in the old snowpack necessitate caution and restraint.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>As a consequence of warming during the day, the likelihood of moist and wet avalanches being released will increase in particular on steep sunny slopes below approximately 2600 m. &lt;br/&gt; Dry avalanches can be released in deeper layers also.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The upper section of the snowpack is hard and its surface has a strong crust. &lt;br/&gt; Precarious weak layers exist in the old snowpack especially on steep northwest, north and northeast facing slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
          <tendencyComment>As a consequence of warming during the day the prevalence of the avalanche prone locations will increase as the day progresses.</tendencyComment>
        </BulletinMeasurements>
